OL,3,CTata Steel's plans for new electric
OL,4,Carc furnace in Port Talbot given go-
OL,5,Cahead
OL,7,F"This 1.25-billion-pound investment is
OL,8,Fthe most significant investment made
OL,9,Fin the UK steel industry in decades.
OL,10,FThe facility will secure high-quality
OL,11,Fsteel production, preserve thousands
OL,12,Fof jobs and safeguard steel making in
OL,13,FPort Talbot for generations to come."
OL,15,FThe plans come after Tata Steel closed
OL,16,Fthe last blast furnace on the Port
OL,17,FTalbot steelworks site in September
OL,18,F2024, putting over 2,800 jobs at risk
OL,19,Fand marking the end of traditional
OL,20,Fsteel-making in the town.
